					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You're dealing with the fundamental problem of two masters: the frame rate and sample rate. You're going to have to slave one to the other (work this out on paper until you can see that there's no way around this). It's easy to make the frame rate a slave to the sample rate, and much less noticeable than changes in sample rate. A simple method is to make the frame rate slightly higher than the corresponding sample rate (i.e. 61 FPS), then have your graphics wait until there is no more than a few frames of audio waiting to play before displaying a frame (otherwise you'll have the sound playing too late).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

